ğŸš€ Quick Start
Prerequisites
Before running this project, make sure you have installed:

.NET 8.0 SDK (Required)

Visual Studio Code (Recommended) or any code editor

Git (for cloning the repository)

Step 1: Clone the Repository
bash
git clone https://github.com/RanaFarhanIjaz/Travel-Experience.git
cd Travel-Experience
Step 2: Get Groq API Key (For AI Features)
Go to Groq Console

Sign up for a free account

Create a new API key from the dashboard

Copy your API key

Step 3: Configure API Key
Open Program.cs and replace the placeholder with your actual Groq API key:

csharp
// In Program.cs, find this line and update it:
var apiKey = "your-actual-groq-api-key-here"; // â† Replace this with your key
Step 4: Run the Application
bash
# Restore NuGet packages
dotnet restore

# Build the project
dotnet build

# Run the application
dotnet run
Step 5: Access the Application
Open your web browser and navigate to:

text
https://localhost:7000
or

text
http://localhost:5000
Step 6: Default Login Credentials
Use these credentials to test the application:

Email: admin@travel.com

Password: admin123

