ğŸ› Troubleshooting
Common Issues and Solutions
1. Port Already in Use

bash
dotnet run --urls="https://localhost:7001"
2. Database Issues

bash
rm travelshare.db
dotnet run
3. Build Errors

bash
dotnet clean
dotnet build
4. API Key Issues

Ensure Groq API key is correctly set in Program.cs

Check internet connection for API calls

Verify Groq account is active

Error Messages and Fixes
"Couldn't find .NET SDK"

Install .NET 8.0 SDK from here

"API Key invalid"

Get a new API key from Groq Console

"Database is locked"

Stop the application (Ctrl+C) and restart

